### 5. For the causal effect of question 3…

**a. Based on your selected DAG (2b), what linear regression model should be used to estimate the causal effect correctly and why?**

```{r}
# Valid adjustment sets
adjustmentSets(kang)
```

Apart from the direct effect of BC -> DS there only is one other, indirect, effect from BC -> TL -> AB -> DS. This means there is an open chain structure. When conditioning on the mediators TL and AB, BC and DS become independent given {TL, AB}, resulting in a blocked path. This means that only marginal causal effect of BC on DS would be estimated, and not the total (direct + indirect) causal effect. Given this and the fact that there are no confounders, the prima facie lm is the correct linear model to estimate the causal effect of BC on DS.

**b. Estimate the causal effect with this regression model (with your continuous cause variable). Discuss the results.**

Based on the prima facie regression model, that also seems to reflect the true causal relationship, the causal effect of BC on DS is 0.34.

